History















Country Page




Search










	History

 





	History

 
A History of Growth
Mirae Asset was founded in 1997 in the wake of the Asian currency crisis with a vision of and dedication to serving our clients, helping them build wealth for life. Our endeavor to expand overseas began in 2003 with the establishment of our Hong Kong office, which has become the backbone of our Asian and Emerging Market investment capabilities. Since the inception of that office, we have consistently enhanced our coverage and presence in the emerging markets and are now one of the world's largest emerging market investors.
We are committed to securing future levers of growth and providing value to our clients, as evidenced in our milestones.
March 2015Asia Fund-Class I (MILAX) won the 2015 Lipper Fund Award “Best Fund Over 3 Years” in the Pacific Ex-Japan Category.
September 2013Mirae Asset Discovery Funds reach 3-year anniversary.
June 2012Mirae Asset trademarks "Great Consumer" in the US.
June 2011Mirae Asset Global Investments (Taiwan) established.
September 2010Mirae Asset Discovery Funds launched in the US.
April 2010Harvard Business School selects Mirae Asset Financial Group as case study subject in "International Entrepreneurship" course.
September 2009Mirae Asset Global Investments agrees to form an asset management joint venture in China.
April 2008Mirae Asset Global Investments (USA) established.Mirae Asset Global Investments (Brazil) established.
March 2007Mirae Asset Global Investments (United Kingdom) established.
November 2006Mirae Asset Global Investments (India) established.
September 2006Mirae Asset MAPS Global Investments opens Vietnam office.
December 2003Mirae Asset Global Investments (HK) established.
November 2001Mirae Asset Global Investments selected as Korean National Pension Service manager.
July 2001Mirae Asset Global Investments launches Korea's first equity mutual fund.
December 1998Mirae Asset Global Investments established.
August 1997Mirae Asset Investment Advisory established.













