	Awards and recognitions

 





	Industry recognition

 
Harvard Business School Case Study
In 2012 Mirae Asset was the first Asian asset management company to be selected by Harvard Business School as a case study for their MBA program. The study looked at how, within just a decade, Mirae Asset had successfully become a renowned firm in an industry dominated by large traditional conglomerates.
As an organization originating from the emerging markets, Mirae Asset's story has captured the attention of investors worldwide.
"It is very important to have two perspectives.One; observe what is going on in the present. The other; look to the future.To be a successful entrepreneur, you need to do both."
Hyeon-Joo ParkChairman and Founder of Mirae Asset.













