Mirae Asset Group - Wikipedia






















 






Mirae Asset Group

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Mirae Asset Global Investments
미래에셋금융그룹





Type

Private company


Industry
Financial services


Founded
1997


Headquarters
Seoul, South Korea


Products
Mutual funds, Trading & Investing, Retirement & Planning


AUM
US $100.5 billion (Mar 2017)



Number of employees

675 Total; 152 Investment Professionals (Mar 2017)


Website
www.miraeasset.com


Mirae Asset Financial Group is an independent financial services group in Asia, headquartered in Seoul, South Korea. While the group’s core business is asset management, it also provides comprehensive financial services in the areas of wealth management and life insurance. Mirae Asset was founded by Hyeon Joo Park in 1997 and introduced the very first mutual funds to Korean retail investors in 1998.
Mirae Asset Global Investments Group is the asset management arm of Mirae Asset Financial Group. It is one of the largest investors in emerging market equities.[1] With approximately 675 employees, including around 150 dedicated investment professionals (as of 31 Mar 2017), Mirae Asset Global Investments Group has a presence in Australia, Brazil, Canada, China, Colombia, Hong Kong, India, Korea, Taiwan, the U.K., the United States and Vietnam. The firm manages over US$100 billion in assets globally (as of 31 Mar 2017).[2]



Contents


1 Chairman
2 Milestones [3]
3 Awards [10]
4 Other businesses
5 Notes and references
6 See also
7 External links



Chairman[edit]
Hyeon Joo Park is the founder and Chairman of Mirae Asset Financial Group. He established the Group in 1997, amidst the Asian Financial Crisis and was the first to launch retail mutual funds in South Korea in 1998
Park earned a bachelor's degree in business administration from Korea University and attended the Advanced Management Program at Harvard Business School in 2002
Milestones [3][edit]
2016

Mirae Asset acquires leading securities firm KDB Daewoo Securities, rebranded as Mirae Asset Daewoo[4]
Mirae Asset wins 2016 Asian Private Banker Asset Management Awards for Excellence “Best Fund Provider - Global Emerging Market Equity”[5]

2015

Mirae Asset completes development of Korea's first Four Seasons Hotel in downtown Seoul
Mirae Asset wins 2015 Lipper Fund Awards for Asia Pacific Equity, Asia Great Consumer, and Asia Funds in HK, Taiwan, and US[6]

2014

Mirae Asset launches Horizons Korea KOSPI 200 ETF, the lowest cost Korea ETF in the US market featuring the broadest Korean index exposure[7]

2013

Mirae Asset launches Horizons S&P 500 Covered Call ETF, Horizons’ first US-listed ETF
Mirae Asset launches CSI300 Enhanced Index Fund, the China JV’s first mutual fund

2012

Mirae Asset Global Investments becomes the largest fixed income fund manager in Korea[8]
Mirae Asset establishes Korea’s first joint venture asset management company in China - Mirae Asset Huachen Fund Management
Mirae Asset Global Investments merges with Mirae Asset MAPS Global Investments, its sister company specializing in alternative investments

2011

Mirae Asset Financial Group agreed to acquire 85% of Betapro Management Inc. BetaPro, together with its subsidiary Alphapro, manage the Horizons family of exchange traded funds, the largest ETF family in Canada with more than 70 ETFs listed on the Toronto Stock Exchange and C$3 billion (US$3.1 billion) in Assets under Management
Mirae Asset Global Investments acquires 60% of TLG Asset Management, a fund management subsidiary of Taiwan Life Insurance
Mirae Asset Private Equity, Fila Korea, National Pension Service of Korea and Korea Development Bank agree to buy Acushnet Company, owner of leading golf brands Titleist and FootJoy[9]
Mirae Asset launches iPhone application focused on “Emerging Markets”
Mirae Asset TIGER KOSPI 200 listed in HK

2010

Mirae Asset launches US-domiciled funds
Harvard Business School chooses Mirae Asset’s story and the entrepreneurship of Chairman Park Hyeon Joo for a case study

2009

Mirae Asset Global Investments signs an agreement to form an asset management joint venture in China

2008

Mirae Asset was recognized as the largest investor in emerging markets
Mirae Asset’s SICAV Luxembourg-domiciled funds were launched
Mirae Asset Global Investments (Brazil) was established
Mirae Asset Global Investments (USA) was established

2007

Mirae Asset Global Investments (UK) was established

2006

Mirae Asset Global Investments (India) was established

2005

Mirae Asset launches Korea’s first overseas investment (ex-Korea) fund Mirae Asset Retirement Pension Institute established

2004

Mirae Asset Investment Education & Research Center was established
Mirae Asset MAPS Global Investments was established through the acquisition of a local asset management company

2003

Mirae Asset Global Investments (HK), the first global operation based in Hong Kong, was established

2001

Selected as external manager of the National Pension Service (NPS) of Korea

1998

Korea’s first mutual investment fund was launched by Mirae Asset

1997

Mirae Asset Global Investments was established

